Wayne Duvenage from the Organisation Undoing Tax Abuse speaks to eNCA. #Dstv403 JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng Premier David Makhura will deliver his State of the Province Address (SOPA) on Monday. On the minds of many motorists is the issue of e-tolls. WATCH: Gauteng ANC to continue push to scrap e-tolls On Saturday, the ANC in Gauteng vowed to continue in its fight to have e-tolls scrapped. The party says the government needs to come up with an alternative plan. READ: Joburg residents air Premier concerns ahead of Sopa Wayne Duvenage from the Organisation Undoing Tax Abuse (Outa) says e-tolls are long overdue to be scrapped. "The e-toll system was a huge mistake, I think they know that," said Duvenage. "They should make the decision to pull the plug."